<section id="research">
  <span class="hero-ornament"></span>
  <h2 class="research-title">Research at The Epoch Institute</h2>
  <p class="research-subtitle">Interactive tools and in-depth profiles for studying civilisational trajectories across time.</p>
  <div class="research-grid">

    <a href="/explorer" class="research-card" style="text-decoration:none;">
      <div class="research-card-icon">◈</div>
      <h3 class="research-card-title">Interactive Empire Explorer</h3>
      <p class="research-card-desc">Ninety-four civilisations. Five millennia. Explore normalised power trajectories across territory, military capacity, economic output, governance, cultural influence, and geopolitical reach — filterable by region and era.</p>
      <span class="research-card-cta">Launch Explorer →</span>
    </a>

    <a href="/profiles" class="research-card" style="text-decoration:none;">
      <div class="research-card-icon">🏛</div>
      <h3 class="research-card-title">Empire Profile &amp; Summary</h3>
      <p class="research-card-desc">Detailed chronicles of all 94 civilisations — founding, economy, military, governance, global impact, and decline — illustrated with historical emblems and supported by peer-reviewed references.</p>
      <span class="research-card-cta">Browse Profiles →</span>
    </a>

    <a href="/research-series" class="research-card" style="text-decoration:none;">
      <div class="research-card-icon">◎</div>
      <h3 class="research-card-title">Research Series</h3>
      <p class="research-card-desc">Thematic essay series exploring the structural forces behind civilisational rise and collapse — from administrative architecture and economic networks to military innovation and cultural diffusion.</p>
      <span class="research-card-cta">Read Series →</span>
    </a>

    <a href="/dataset" class="research-card" style="text-decoration:none;">
      <div class="research-card-icon">⊞</div>
      <h3 class="research-card-title">Open Dataset</h3>
      <p class="research-card-desc">The full empire trajectory dataset — 94 civilisations, five millennia of normalised power scores — freely available for academic and research use under a Creative Commons Attribution licence.</p>
      <span class="research-card-cta">Download Data →</span>
    </a>

  </div>
